body.content: Bartomoleo — At the end of every day, Dunkin’ Donuts throws the unsold donuts and bread in the garbage. But is this the only way? Maricela doesn’t think so. They started this petition to urge Dunkin’ Donuts to stop wasting perfectly good food and instead donate to homeless shelters. Add your name now if you think food shouldn’t go to waste when people are going hungry. Dunkin Donuts giving waste donuts and breads to the homeless shelters 25,101 have signed maricela vasquez’s petition. Let’s get to 35,000! Every day countless donuts and various types of bread are just being thrown out in the trash. A waste, even a disgrace. And the next day it’s the same process. If it’s busy, in midday they run out of a specific product usually they remake them and double it. Which adds to more waste when no one is buying them anymore. It has to end, the waste count is building up while people are wondering when their next meal is.  Sign now with a click https://click.e.change.org/f/a/iPQULfEEGJVmrHJhK-_T5w~~/AANj1QA~~~ Visit petition page https://click.e.change.org/f/a/3tXNOU5tBiAz-uQ6SBtWXQ~~/AANj1QA~~~ At Change.org, we believe in the voice of everyday people.
